def: The twelfth part of a troy pound.
The lesser spotted woodpecker (Dendrocopus minor); -- calledalso tapperer, tabberer, little wood pie, barred woodpecker, woodtapper, hickwall, and pump borer. [Prov. Eng.]
The milk secreted just before, or directly after, the birth ofa child or of the young of an animal; colostrum.
A division of vermiform gastropod mollusks, without a shell,belonging to the Isopleura.
Furnished with fleshy cups for adhering to bodies, ascuttlefish, etc.
To deprive of the tongue. [Obs.] Davies (Holy Roode).
A layer of tiles forming a corona for a wall.
A curve traced by a point in the circumference of a circlewhich rolls on the convex side of a fixed circle.
A dealer in aphorisms. [Used in derogation or contempt.]Milton.
